            h2.section-heading Why AngularJS?
            blockquote
              | AngularJS lets you extend HTML vocabulary for your application. The resulting environment is extraordinarily expressive, readable, and quick to develop. - angularJS.org
            p
              | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;AngularJS is an open-source MVC framework developed in 2009 by Google for CRUD (create, read, update, delete) single page web applications (SPA’s). It improves HTML, reduces the amount of code you would otherwise have to write, makes data-binding a breeze, lowers possibility for error and makes many common tasks effortless. Below is an example of plain JavaScript vs. AngularJS:
            span.caption.text-muted Plain JavaScript
